{"analysis_path": "obsidian-vault/analysis/ICLR_2026/Forest-Based_Graph_Learning_for_Semi-Supervised_Node_Classification.md", "core_operator": "生成树的选择分布：通过提高边缘同质性估计质量，可以诱导出偏向高同质性树的分布，从而使森林中的树以更高的概率包含有利的同质性边，进而提升全局消息传递的质量。", "datasets": ["Cora", "Pubmed", "Cornell", "Texas"], "method_groups": ["Representation / Self-Supervised / Transfer", "Generative / Diffusion / Flow"], "methods": ["FGL", "Forest-based Graph Learning", "FGL (Forest-based Graph Learning)"], "paper_link": "https://openreview.net/forum?id=5asbtzIVpS", "pdf_ref": "obsidian-vault/paperPDFs/ICLR_2026/Forest-Based_Graph_Learning_for_Semi-Supervised_Node_Classification.pdf", "primary_logic": "将图上的消息传递重新诠释为在生成树（森林）上的传输，利用生成树既能够全局覆盖所有节点、又具有极小边数的特点，同时通过同质性引导的采样和线性时间的递归聚合，优雅地打破了成本与全局感受野的权衡。", "project_link": "", "source": "paper_list.csv+analysis", "tags": ["topic/representation_self_supervised_transfer", "topic/generative_models_diffusion/graph_neural_networks", "topic/generative_models_diffusion"], "title": "Forest-Based Graph Learning for Semi-Supervised Node Classification", "topics": ["Representation / Self-Supervised / Transfer", "Generative Models / Diffusion"], "venue": "ICLR", "year": 2026}
{"analysis_path": "obsidian-vault/analysis/ICLR_2026/HGNet_Scalable_Foundation_Model_for_Automated_Knowledge_Graph_Generation_from_Scientific_Literature.md", "core_operator": "通过正交语义分解（OSD）提取领域不变的语义转折信号；多尺度TCQK注意力强制头部分别捕获不同长度的n-gram模式；层次化三通道消息传递（父、子、对等）显式建模概念间的方向性关系；可微层次损失和连续抽象场损失强制图谱形成有向无环图并沿抽象轴有序排列。", "datasets": ["SciERC", "SciER", "BioRED", "SemEval", "SPHERE"], "method_groups": ["Representation / Self-Supervised / Transfer", "Generative / Diffusion / Flow"], "methods": ["HGNet", "Z-NERD", "HGNet（包含 Z-NERD 零样本实体识别和 HGNet 层次关系抽取）"], "paper_link": "https://openreview.net/forum?id=NWd53rltx8", "pdf_ref": "obsidian-vault/paperPDFs/ICLR_2026/HGNet_Scalable_Foundation_Model_for_Automated_Knowledge_Graph_Generation_from_Scientific_Literature.pdf", "primary_logic": "将自注意力泛化为稀疏实体图上的多通道层次消息传递，并在欧氏空间中引入可学习的抽象场向量，使模型能够捕捉科学概念之间的深层抽象层次，而非仅仅依赖表面共现，从而实现轻量、零样本、全局一致的层次知识图谱构建。", "project_link": "", "source": "paper_list.csv+analysis", "tags": ["topic/representation_self_supervised_transfer", "topic/generative_models_diffusion/graph_neural_networks", "topic/generative_models_diffusion"], "title": "HGNet: Scalable Foundation Model for Automated Knowledge Graph Generation from Scientific Literature", "topics": ["Representation / Self-Supervised / Transfer", "Generative Models / Diffusion"], "venue": "ICLR", "year": 2026}
